@startuml
title SmoresUnderflow - Deployment Sequence Diagram

actor "DevOps Engineer" as DevOps
participant "Ansible\nController" as Ansible
participant "Target\nInstance" as Instance
database "MongoDB" as Mongo
database "Redis\nCache" as Redis
database "ElasticSearch" as Elastic
participant "RabbitMQ" as Rabbit
participant "Nginx" as Nginx
participant "PM2\nProcess Manager" as PM2
participant "su-accounts\nService" as Accounts
participant "su-users\nService" as Users
participant "su-questions\nService" as Questions
participant "qu-questions\nQueue Service" as QQuestions
participant "qu-answers\nQueue Service" as QAnswers
participant "su-search\nService" as Search
participant "su-media\nService" as Media
participant "su-frontend\nReact App" as Frontend

DevOps -> Ansible: Execute ansible.yml playbook
activate Ansible

Ansible -> Instance: Connect via SSH
activate Instance

Ansible -> Instance: Run instances.yml\n(install common packages)
Instance -> Instance: Install dependencies\n(Node.js, npm, etc.)

Ansible -> Instance: Run cache.yml\n(configure Redis)
Instance -> Redis: Install and configure Redis
activate Redis
Redis --> Instance: Redis ready
Instance --> Ansible: Cache configured

Ansible -> Instance: Run search.yml\n(configure ElasticSearch)
Instance -> Elastic: Install and configure\nElasticSearch & Kibana
activate Elastic
Elastic --> Instance: ElasticSearch ready
Instance --> Ansible: Search configured

Ansible -> Instance: Install RabbitMQ
Instance -> Rabbit: Configure message queues
activate Rabbit
Rabbit --> Instance: RabbitMQ ready

Ansible -> Instance: Install MongoDB
Instance -> Mongo: Configure database
activate Mongo
Mongo --> Instance: MongoDB ready

Ansible -> Instance: Deploy microservices code
Instance --> Ansible: Code deployed

Ansible -> Instance: Configure Nginx
Instance -> Nginx: Setup reverse proxy\nand load balancing
activate Nginx
Nginx --> Instance: Nginx configured

Ansible -> PM2: Start su-accounts service
activate PM2
PM2 -> Accounts: Start process
activate Accounts
Accounts -> Mongo: Connect to database
Accounts -> Redis: Connect to cache
Accounts --> PM2: Service running

Ansible -> PM2: Start su-users service
PM2 -> Users: Start process
activate Users
Users -> Mongo: Connect to database
Users -> Redis: Connect to cache
Users --> PM2: Service running

Ansible -> PM2: Start su-questions service
PM2 -> Questions: Start process
activate Questions
Questions -> Mongo: Connect to database
Questions -> Redis: Connect to cache
Questions -> Rabbit: Connect to message queue
Questions --> PM2: Service running

Ansible -> PM2: Start qu-questions queue service
PM2 -> QQuestions: Start process
activate QQuestions
QQuestions -> Mongo: Connect to database
QQuestions -> Rabbit: Subscribe to question queue
QQuestions -> Elastic: Connect to search index
QQuestions --> PM2: Service running

Ansible -> PM2: Start qu-answers queue service
PM2 -> QAnswers: Start process
activate QAnswers
QAnswers -> Mongo: Connect to database
QAnswers -> Rabbit: Subscribe to answer queue
QAnswers --> PM2: Service running

Ansible -> PM2: Start su-search service
PM2 -> Search: Start process
activate Search
Search -> Mongo: Connect to database
Search -> Redis: Connect to cache
Search -> Elastic: Connect to search index
Search --> PM2: Service running

Ansible -> PM2: Start su-media service
PM2 -> Media: Start process
activate Media
Media -> Mongo: Connect to database
Media -> Redis: Connect to cache
Media --> PM2: Service running

Ansible -> Instance: Deploy frontend build
Instance -> Frontend: Deploy React app to Nginx
activate Frontend
Frontend --> Instance: Frontend deployed

Ansible -> Nginx: Configure routing\nto microservices
Nginx --> Ansible: Load balancing active

Ansible --> DevOps: Deployment complete\nAll services running

deactivate Ansible
deactivate Instance
deactivate PM2

note right of Nginx
  Nginx handles:
  - Load balancing across instances
  - Reverse proxy to microservices
  - Serving static frontend assets
end note

note right of PM2
  PM2 manages:
  - Process lifecycle
  - Auto-restart on failure
  - Multiple instances per service
end note

@enduml
